This paper deals with the problem of testing compatibility of semi-labeled trees, which is a fundamental problem in computational biology. The problem involves finding a tree that respects the ancestor/descendant relationships and clusterings implied by the input trees. This problem has applications in many areas of computer science, including data structures, algorithms, computational geometry, and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
